    <h1>Features</h1>

    
    

    <div class="text-container">
        <p>
            <!-- <strong>What is Loot?</strong><br> -->
            <strong>1. Decentralized</strong><br> 
            Loot Crypto Coin is a fully decentralized cryptocurrency, which means no central authority controls the network. This allows for a trustless environment where users can interact directly with one another, ensuring transparency and autonomy in every transaction.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-container">
        <p>
            <strong>2. Node Hosting</strong> <br>
            Anyone can participate in the Loot Crypto Coin network by hosting a node. By hosting a node, users help secure the network and validate transactions, contributing to the overall robustness of the system. This open participation empowers individuals to engage directly in the decentralized ecosystem.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-container">
        <p>
            <strong>3. Security</strong><br> 
            Security is at the core of Loot Crypto Coin. Our blockchain ensures all transactions are cryptographically secured, and the decentralized network eliminates single points of failure. Each transaction is validated by nodes, reducing the chances of fraud or attacks.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-container">
        <p>
                <strong>4. Peer-to-Peer Transactions</strong><br>
            Loot Crypto Coin operates on a peer-to-peer network, enabling direct transactions between users without intermediaries. This ensures lower transaction fees and quicker processing times, while also allowing for greater privacy and control over user funds.
        </p>
    </div>

  <script>
    function accordion_toggle(target) {

    // Create a reference to all sections using
    // a class name.
    var divsToHide = document.getElementsByClassName("accordion-section"); 
    // Loop through each section
    for(var i = 0; i < divsToHide.length; i++){
        // Hide esch section
        divsToHide[i].style.display = "none"; 
    }

    // Create a reference to an element with the
    // same name as the target variable
    var content = document.getElementById(target);

    // Check if the content is currently displayed
    if (content.style.display === "block"){
        // Hide the content
        content.style.display = "none";
    } else {
        // Display the content
        content.style.display = "block";
    }
  }


  </script>
